
[1]vari

   VA'RI, n. In zoology, a species of quadruped, the maucauco or Lemur
   catta of Linne, having its tail marked with rings of black and white; a
   native of Madagascar. The vari of Buffon is the black maucauco, L.
   macaco of Linne, with the neck bearded, like a ruff.
